title: Make VarZeroVec format configurable
body:
This finishes the 1.0 polish work necessary for https://github.com/unicode-org/icu4x/issues/1410, switching us over to Index16 by default with Index32 being used for BlobDataProvider.


Stuff that should be done soon but is not necessary for ICU4X 1.0:
 - ZeroMap support (we didn't need this, and it can be added incrementally)
 - Format strategy support in custom derive
 - Actual nice errors for VZV mutation operations
 - Perhaps clean up the code to not cast to usize as often (and instead cast to the relevant index type)


Stuff to do eventually:
 - Introduce an "Auto" strategy (will need a rewrite of the code)

title: Add icu_timezone crate
body:
cc @nordzilla @samchen61661

fixes https://github.com/unicode-org/icu4x/issues/2145

This moves:

 - `TimeZone` (née `MockTimeZone`)
 - `GmtOffset`
 - `MetaZonePeriodV1`

over to a new `icu_timezone` crate. The WIP time zone resolver code should also live in this crate when it lands.

One thing I'm not sure about is what the new error variants shoudl be. The current status is that `DateTimeError` (from `icu_calendar`) which does not depend on `icu_timezone`, contains a single `InvalidTimeZoneOffset` error, that `mock::parse_zoned_gregorian_from_str` can return. `icu_timezone::TimeZoneError` has a bunch of variants copied over.

I'm not sure if this is ideal, especially since `DateTimeError` now contains an error variant that is irrelevant to that crate. We could make `icu_calendar` depend on `icu_timezone` and nest the error, or we could have `parse_zoned_gregorian_from_str` return a different error type.

Renaming:

- `UnicodePropertyMapV1 -> PropertyCodePointMapV1`
